From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] fix: skip QSPI flash pm_device_action_run, hangs main

WR_TRACE printk diagnostics from patch 0020 narrowed main's hang
window to the block between
  printk("WR_TRACE: 1_dcdc_done")   // visible in serial capture
and
  printk("WR_TRACE: 2_qspi_done")   // never appears

The intervening code is the QSPI flash deep-sleep call:

    const struct device *flash_dev = DEVICE_DT_GET(DT_NODELABEL(p25q16h));
    if (device_is_ready(flash_dev)) {
        err = pm_device_action_run(flash_dev, PM_DEVICE_ACTION_SUSPEND);
        ...
    } else {
        LOG_ERR("QSPI flash device not ready");
    }

CONFIG_SPI_NOR was assigned 'y' in our overlay but unsatisfied deps in
NCS v2.7 (FLASH && DT_HAS_JEDEC_SPI_NOR_ENABLED) leave it at 'n'.
Without SPI_NOR, no driver binds to the p25q16h DT node. DEVICE_DT_GET
still returns a non-null device pointer (statically generated), but
device_is_ready() may spin or pm_device_action_run() may walk a
half-initialised pm_device structure and lock up.

Drop the QSPI deep-sleep path entirely. It is a power-saving nicety
specific to the omi production hardware (where the QSPI flash is
unused after boot). On DK1+SPISD with SD-only mode we run from USB,
so skipping it is harmless.

This patch must be applied AFTER 0020 (WR_TRACE checkpoints).
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
@@ -150,16 +150,8 @@ int main(void)
     LOG_INF("Model: %s", CONFIG_BT_DIS_MODEL);
     LOG_INF("Firmware revision: %s", CONFIG_BT_DIS_FW_REV_STR);
     LOG_INF("Hardware revision: %s", CONFIG_BT_DIS_HW_REV_STR);
-    // Force QSPI flash into deep sleep mode
-    const struct device *flash_dev = DEVICE_DT_GET(DT_NODELABEL(p25q16h));
-    if (device_is_ready(flash_dev)) {
-        err = pm_device_action_run(flash_dev, PM_DEVICE_ACTION_SUSPEND);
-        if (err) {
-            LOG_ERR("Failed to suspend QSPI flash: %d", err);
-        }
-    } else {
-        LOG_ERR("QSPI flash device not ready");
-    }
+    /* patch 0021: skipped — pm_device_action_run hangs main when
+     * SPI_NOR=n (deps unsatisfied in NCS v2.7). See patch header. */
     printk("WR_TRACE: 2_qspi_done\n");
     LOG_PRINTK("\n");
     LOG_INF("Initializing LEDs...\n");
